	Communication Specificatioins:

		SOAP 	[Service Oriented Architecure Protocol]
		REST	[representational State Transfer]
		JSON 	[Javascript Object Notation]

	SOAP
		-services consumer sends xml request
		-Server provider sends xml response
	
		Request:
				<Products>
					<product>
						<Category>Electronics</Category>
					</product>
				</Products>
		Response:
				<Products>
					<product>
						<id>4</id>
						<Name>Tv</Name>
						<Category><Electronics</Category>
					</product>
					.....
				</Products>
					
	REST
			-Consumer sends a query request.
			-Provider sends XML or JSON.
			
		Request:
				https://server.com/data/products?category=electronics
				http://server.com /data/products/electronics

		Response
			[
				{id:4, Name:'TV", Category:"Electronics"},
				.....
			]
	
	JSON 
		-consumer sends json request.
		-provider sends JSON response.

